game:stone-bake-oven-text:
Stone Bake Oven
'When man made fire with nothing but sticks and stones it was all in the hope that one day he could bake bread in an oven like this'
Preparation
The most basic of oven with this mod only requires 3 copper plates and any type of stone you want (Rock, Polished Rock, Cobblestone and Stone Brick - blocks).
Craft
1 Oven Baking Space
1 Oven Heat Distribution
1 Oven Heat Source
Creation
To create the most basic of oven you place down the Oven Heat Source then proceed to place the Oven Heat Distribution block to the left or right of the Oven Heat Source. You then place infront of the Oven Heat Distribution the Oven Baking Space.
This is the most basic oven setup and can be expanded upon (see mod DB page for more info or below for a rough guide).
Usage
The oven works by taking heat from the Oven Heat Source block and transfering it to the Oven Baking Space blocks through the Oven Heat Distribution blocks. This is done by placeing burnable material into the Oven Heat Source block and lighting it with a torch. Finally you place the baking items you want to bake upon the Oven Baking Space exactly like you would a clay oven and wait for it to bake.
Variation
There are a few diffrent layouts you can try with the only limit being that the Oven Baking Spaces get colder as you go further out but retain their 300C for around 4 'block' placments outward from the central Oven Heat Source.
Please experiment with adding additional Oven Heat Distribution blocks and Oven Baking Space blocks.
NOTE- You will only ever need 1 Oven Heat Source within the setup unless you are making an oven to feed a thousand seraphs.
Q&A
Why use this over the Clay Oven?
This Oven on testing cooks quicker but also burns less fuel on larger baking jobs when it is up to heat (this is offset by higher creation costs both material and tech wise).
Why so simple?
The reason why the oven's design is so simple is to allow the user to chisel the blocks around it aswell as create an oven casing that they desire.
Can this bake modded items?
This oven does (at least in testing) allow you to bake ANY item that would be baked normally within the vanilla Clay Oven.
